WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.320
[THEME MUSIC]
(SINGING) Let's go!

00:01.320 --> 00:06.410
Go on a run, run for our
lives will tear a hole

00:06.410 --> 00:09.480
in every fence and every wall.

00:09.480 --> 00:11.280
Run through the fields.

00:11.280 --> 00:13.320
Run wild and free.

00:13.320 --> 00:16.840
And grab a piece of
every radish that we see.

00:16.840 --> 00:18.810
Go day and night.

00:18.810 --> 00:20.780
Go for it all.

00:20.780 --> 00:22.260
It's time to fly.

00:22.260 --> 00:23.740
Come on, the wind's
begun to blow.

00:23.740 --> 00:27.680
Let's go. 'Cause you and I, we
weren't made for going slow.

00:27.680 --> 00:28.670
Let's go.

00:28.670 --> 00:30.150
Adventure calls again.

00:30.150 --> 00:30.930
[INAUDIBLE] Come on.

00:30.930 --> 00:31.630
Let's go.

00:31.630 --> 00:32.409
Peter Rabbit.

00:32.409 --> 00:33.100
Let's go.

00:33.100 --> 00:34.580
Peter Rabbit.

00:34.580 --> 00:35.570
Let's go.

00:35.570 --> 00:36.560
Peter Rabbit.

00:36.560 --> 00:37.540
Let's go.

00:41.490 --> 00:44.380
NARRATOR: The Tale of
the Dash in the Dark.

00:50.120 --> 00:51.600
Whoa.

00:51.600 --> 01:00.530
[LAUGHING]

01:00.530 --> 01:03.870
And now for the grand finale.

01:08.800 --> 01:09.780
Ta-da!

01:13.720 --> 01:15.190
[CRYING]

01:15.190 --> 01:16.180
Whoa.

01:20.610 --> 01:22.930
I don't understand.

01:22.930 --> 01:24.570
We tried everything.

01:24.570 --> 01:27.550
I'm afraid Cottontail is
just frightened of the dark.

01:27.550 --> 01:29.620
There's nothing to be done
until she grows out of it.

01:29.620 --> 01:31.330
Poor thing.

01:31.330 --> 01:33.460
How is she ever going to sleep?

01:33.460 --> 01:37.509
I really wish
I could help her.

01:37.509 --> 01:39.720
Don't be so hard
on yourself, Peter.

01:39.720 --> 01:43.180
Getting babies to sleep isn't
really a big brothery thing.

01:43.180 --> 01:45.810
It's more of a
big sistery thing.

01:45.810 --> 01:48.600
Just stick to raiding
vegetable patches.

01:48.600 --> 01:50.690
We'll take care of
our little sister.

01:50.690 --> 01:54.160
Isn't that right,
little cottony-wottony.

01:54.160 --> 01:58.580
[CRYING]

01:58.580 --> 02:00.880
There must be
something we can do.

02:00.880 --> 02:05.740
A night light is a big help
when you're afraid of the dark.

02:05.740 --> 02:07.720
At least that's what I've heard.

02:07.720 --> 02:09.970
Have you ever
seen a glow worm?

02:09.970 --> 02:14.470
They light up at night,
don't they, Florence?

02:14.470 --> 02:18.650
A jar full of glow worms would
make a perfect night light.

02:18.650 --> 02:19.620
Lily, you're a genius.

02:22.510 --> 02:24.660
Let's go and catch
some glow worms.

02:24.660 --> 02:25.800
What?

02:25.800 --> 02:27.050
Now?

02:27.050 --> 02:28.040
I didn't mean--

02:28.040 --> 02:29.180
Come on.

02:29.180 --> 02:30.760
But--

02:30.760 --> 02:33.310
(SINGING) Sleep, little baby.

02:33.310 --> 02:35.770
Close your eyes.

02:35.770 --> 02:42.740
Your sisters will
sing you a lullaby.

02:42.740 --> 02:48.220
[CRYING]

02:48.220 --> 02:50.460
I'm going to catch a million--

02:50.460 --> 02:53.120
no, a gazillion-- glow worms.

02:53.120 --> 02:56.090
And I know just
where to find them--

02:56.090 --> 02:57.930
in the woods.

02:57.930 --> 03:00.050
Yeah, wait.

03:00.050 --> 03:02.200
In the woods?

03:02.200 --> 03:04.280
That's right.

03:04.280 --> 03:06.250
At night?

03:06.250 --> 03:07.640
Of course.

03:07.640 --> 03:10.420
There's nothing more fun
than a nighttime adventure.

03:10.420 --> 03:13.060
No, nothing.

03:13.060 --> 03:14.710
I love nighttime.

03:14.710 --> 03:16.890
It's so dark.

03:16.890 --> 03:20.130
Oh, I can't wait to
catch my first glow worm.

03:20.130 --> 03:21.500
Let's hop to it.

03:29.010 --> 03:29.710
[CROAKS]

03:29.710 --> 03:31.900
What was that?

03:31.900 --> 03:33.650
It's just a toad, Benjamin.

03:36.360 --> 03:40.200
[STRIDULATING]

03:40.200 --> 03:42.310
What was that?

03:42.310 --> 03:44.760
It's only a cricket, Benjamin.

03:44.760 --> 03:47.170
I knew that.

03:47.170 --> 03:47.870
Just testing.

03:50.450 --> 03:52.110
What was that?

03:52.110 --> 03:54.190
It's you, Benjamin.

03:54.190 --> 03:56.340
You've got something
stuck to your foot.

03:59.630 --> 04:01.470
Are you all right?

04:01.470 --> 04:02.760
Me?

04:02.760 --> 04:04.530
Yeah, never better.

04:04.530 --> 04:05.970
Why do you ask?

04:05.970 --> 04:08.030
Want to hold my hand?

04:08.030 --> 04:09.080
Yes, please.

04:14.950 --> 04:19.019
Look, are those--

04:19.019 --> 04:20.070
Glow worms.

04:23.960 --> 04:27.050
Wait for me.

04:27.050 --> 04:28.770
Just look at them.

04:33.110 --> 04:35.710
They're wonderful.

04:35.710 --> 04:38.090
Let's get a jarful
for Cottontail.

04:38.090 --> 04:40.159
[MUSIC PLAYING]
(SINGING) Off you go.

04:40.159 --> 04:40.960
No time to lose.

04:40.960 --> 04:42.659
You best be on your way.

04:45.680 --> 04:47.030
Proceed with care.

04:47.030 --> 04:49.890
Think fast and stay
aware and you'll succeed

04:49.890 --> 04:52.790
at what you're trying to do.

04:52.790 --> 04:55.580
The golden [INAUDIBLE]
is waiting there for you.

04:59.990 --> 05:02.900
There that's the last of them.

05:02.900 --> 05:04.960
It's the perfect nightlight.

05:04.960 --> 05:07.560
You know, glow worms
really do help you

05:07.560 --> 05:09.750
feel less afraid of the dark.

05:09.750 --> 05:12.450
I mean, if I were
scared they would,

05:12.450 --> 05:14.370
which I'm definitely not.

05:14.370 --> 05:17.110
Why would you think I'm scared?

05:17.110 --> 05:19.290
OK, then.

05:19.290 --> 05:21.290
Let's take them
home to Cottontail.

05:21.290 --> 05:23.430
Don't worry I'll lead the way.

05:23.430 --> 05:25.230
These woods don't scare me.

05:29.040 --> 05:31.630
Uh, what is that smell?

05:31.630 --> 05:34.800
Oh, it smells
almost as bad as a--

05:34.800 --> 05:35.520
badger.

05:35.520 --> 05:36.480
Oh no.

05:36.480 --> 05:38.890
[SCREAMING]

05:38.890 --> 05:40.570
Give me my dinner.

05:40.570 --> 05:41.870
Dinner?

05:41.870 --> 05:43.720
You eat glow worms?

05:43.720 --> 05:45.790
Course I do.

05:45.790 --> 05:48.460
The only bugs he
can find at night.

05:48.460 --> 05:51.280
What?

05:51.280 --> 05:52.409
Sorry.

05:52.409 --> 05:53.110
You're right.

05:53.110 --> 05:54.159
Not funny.

05:54.159 --> 05:56.740
These glow worms
for my little sister.

05:56.740 --> 05:58.690
She's afraid of the
dark and she needs them.

05:58.690 --> 06:00.290
Give them to him, Peter.

06:00.290 --> 06:03.220
There are enough glow
worms for everyone.

06:03.220 --> 06:04.700
Give them here.

06:04.700 --> 06:06.810
You have to catch us first.

06:14.610 --> 06:16.360
You rotten rabbits.

06:22.860 --> 06:25.260
Wait.

06:25.260 --> 06:28.180
There's one of my dad's
hiding places in here.

06:28.180 --> 06:29.310
Let's hop to it.

06:36.270 --> 06:38.260
Aha!

06:38.260 --> 06:39.130
My dinner.

06:41.730 --> 06:42.970
Oh no.

06:42.970 --> 06:45.530
Brooke's coming straight for us.

06:45.530 --> 06:47.360
How does he know where we are?

06:47.360 --> 06:48.770
It's the light from the jar.

06:48.770 --> 06:49.600
He can see it.

06:49.600 --> 06:50.810
Right.

06:50.810 --> 06:54.440
Abandon log!

06:54.440 --> 06:55.920
Got yah.

06:55.920 --> 06:57.900
Oh, no.

06:57.900 --> 06:58.880
Benjamin.

07:10.760 --> 07:12.630
He'll never be able to
track us through here.

07:16.720 --> 07:18.320
Never say never.

07:18.320 --> 07:19.700
It's the glow worms.

07:22.960 --> 07:24.780
Stop glowing.

07:24.780 --> 07:26.180
Switch off or something.

07:26.180 --> 07:28.390
I don't think they
can help it, Benjamin.

07:28.390 --> 07:30.600
Let's get rid of it, then.

07:30.600 --> 07:31.610
Please.

07:31.610 --> 07:33.580
Throw it away and let's go home.

07:33.580 --> 07:36.360
Cottontail needs
this night light,

07:36.360 --> 07:38.490
and I'm not going
to let her down.

07:38.490 --> 07:40.260
We need a plan.

07:40.260 --> 07:41.850
We're going to
have to be clever.

07:41.850 --> 07:43.020
I'm clever.

07:43.020 --> 07:44.070
And quick.

07:44.070 --> 07:44.940
I'm quick.

07:44.940 --> 07:46.659
And brave.

07:46.659 --> 07:48.310
I'm quick.

07:48.310 --> 07:52.850
And we'll need some of that
string from Lily's pocket.

07:52.850 --> 07:53.630
Yes.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.080
Aha.

07:58.080 --> 07:59.390
Now.

07:59.390 --> 08:03.480
I'll take that [INAUDIBLE] Oh.

08:03.480 --> 08:04.500
Huh.

08:04.500 --> 08:05.480
I'm okay.

08:05.480 --> 08:08.260
Oh, sneaky rabbits.

08:08.260 --> 08:13.310
Oh, well, well, fancy that.

08:13.310 --> 08:15.810
Well, I suppose
you'll do for a snack.

08:15.810 --> 08:16.530
Come here.

08:16.530 --> 08:18.360
Oh, where-- where are you going?

08:18.360 --> 08:19.900
Oh, hold still.

08:19.900 --> 08:25.420
Now let's get that
jar home to Cottontail.

08:25.420 --> 08:27.300
Oh, no.

08:27.300 --> 08:28.710
Oh.

08:28.710 --> 08:31.390
I'll get it.

08:31.390 --> 08:33.169
Let me.

08:33.169 --> 08:40.320
[INAUDIBLE] It's too small.

08:40.320 --> 08:42.570
Benjamin, you're
the best digger.

08:42.570 --> 08:44.690
Maybe you can dig
your way in there.

08:44.690 --> 08:49.530
Um, uh, well, yes.

08:49.530 --> 08:51.720
I'd love to, but--

08:51.720 --> 08:54.870
well, I think there's
something I should tell you.

08:54.870 --> 08:56.940
You're afraid of the dark?

08:56.940 --> 08:59.160
Yes, very.

08:59.160 --> 09:00.120
How did you know?

09:00.120 --> 09:01.740
Lucky guess.

09:01.740 --> 09:05.040
It's OK, Benjamin I was
afraid of the dark too

09:05.040 --> 09:06.030
when I was little.

09:06.030 --> 09:06.730
What?

09:06.730 --> 09:07.430
You?

09:07.430 --> 09:09.920
But you're not
afraid of anything.

09:09.920 --> 09:12.930
Everyone is afraid
of something sometimes.

09:12.930 --> 09:16.510
I always hum to myself
whenever I'm scared.

09:16.510 --> 09:18.730
It makes me feel better somehow.

09:18.730 --> 09:24.220
[HUMMING]

09:24.220 --> 09:25.900
Don't worry, Benjamin.

09:25.900 --> 09:27.340
If you don't want
to go in there,

09:27.340 --> 09:29.540
we'll just have to find
some more glow worms.

09:29.540 --> 09:31.390
If we can.

09:31.390 --> 09:33.960
And if Tommy Brooke
doesn't come back.

09:33.960 --> 09:36.140
Wait.

09:36.140 --> 09:38.980
If you two stopped
being scared,

09:38.980 --> 09:42.580
then so can I. I'm
going to get that jar.

09:42.580 --> 09:44.020
All right.

09:44.020 --> 09:45.360
Hop to it.

09:45.360 --> 09:47.560
You can get those
glow worms, Benjamin.

09:47.560 --> 09:50.320
You're a brave bunny.

09:50.320 --> 09:51.750
Rabbits are brave.

09:51.750 --> 09:52.880
Rabbits are brave.

09:56.780 --> 09:59.490
Oh!

09:59.490 --> 10:00.180
Phew.

10:04.570 --> 10:08.390
Uh, guys, I don't
know about this.

10:08.390 --> 10:09.870
PETER RABBIT: Come on, Benjamin.

10:09.870 --> 10:12.340
You dig tunnels all the time.

10:12.340 --> 10:14.740
But this isn't
one of my tunnels.

10:17.920 --> 10:18.620
Wait!

10:18.620 --> 10:23.570
I-- I think I see it.

10:23.570 --> 10:25.490
I found it.

10:25.490 --> 10:28.850
Yeah.

10:28.850 --> 10:32.220
Well done, Benjamin.

10:32.220 --> 10:34.290
Piece of cake.

10:34.290 --> 10:36.540
I was never really scared.

10:36.540 --> 10:39.500
Um, Benjamin.

10:39.500 --> 10:40.480
Ahh!

10:40.480 --> 10:42.940
Oh!

10:42.940 --> 10:46.080
Shoo.

10:46.080 --> 10:48.530
[MUSIC PLAYING]

10:52.460 --> 10:53.720
Goodnight, Cottontail.

10:57.190 --> 11:00.620
What a very
clever idea, Peter.

11:00.620 --> 11:03.020
Amazing that you
found so many glow

11:03.020 --> 11:04.610
worms right here in the burrow.

11:04.610 --> 11:10.120
Uhhh, yes, well, you see--

11:10.120 --> 11:12.060
Maybe you two should
be getting back home.

11:12.060 --> 11:12.760
Yeah.

11:12.760 --> 11:13.460
Right.

11:16.420 --> 11:19.320
Would you like me to walk
home with you, Benjamin?

11:19.320 --> 11:21.250
It is pretty dark out tonight

11:21.250 --> 11:22.350
No, thanks.

11:22.350 --> 11:23.680
I'll be just fine.

11:23.680 --> 11:25.810
I don't think I'll even
need to hum to myself.

11:25.810 --> 11:26.510
Heh.

11:26.510 --> 11:27.600
Good night, Benjamin.

11:27.600 --> 11:28.300
Bye.

11:34.900 --> 11:37.300
[CROAKS]

11:39.900 --> 11:40.600
[THEME MUSIC]

11:40.600 --> 11:41.500
(SINGING) Peter Rabbit.

11:52.000 --> 11:57.750
Peter Rabbit, Peter
Rabbit, Peter Rabbit.
